    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a concentrated offensive core, anchored by the high-upside matchup for **Luis Robert Jr.** against Edouard Rodriguez. Scoring a 73.98, **Luis Robert Jr.** benefits significantly from a favorable platoon advantage and a premium spot in the order, making him our strongest play of the day despite a slightly suppressed park factor. **Jacob Wilson** (66.74) remains a foundational piece; his ability to set the table from the leadoff spot against the lefty-leaning profile of Ryan Weathers provides high floor and, crucially, the speed upside required to keep pace in our quest for stolen bases. While **Jackson Merrill** (60.31) and **Miguel Vargas** (59.68) round out the lineup, both are buoyed by top-three lineup spots and favorable SP_xERA marks, with **Miguel Vargas** specifically gaining a wind-aided boost that keeps him firmly in the \"Strong\" start category.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision involved balancing the thin profile of **Liam Hicks** (41.33) against the remaining depth. While **Liam Hicks** sits firmly at the bottom of the active lineup, his presence in the cleanup spot provides just enough peripheral value to justify the start over potential utility options. We are effectively punting the bench today, as **Kyle Tucker**, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, **Gunnar Henderson**, and **Andy Pages** are all unavailable due to team off-days, leaving our core reserves like **Jordan Westburg**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Drake Baldwin**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Josh Lowe**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Heliot Ramos**, **Nolan Schanuel**, **Marcell Ozuna**, **Josh Jung**, and **Coby Mayo** in a holding pattern. We have no significant weather flags to report, though **Miguel Vargas** must remain a focal point; his score is tethered to the current wind reports, and any shift in conditions could necessitate a re-evaluation of his ceiling.",
